full_text: Today's anniversary is also a reminder that we have work left to do securing access to voting for all Americans. Congress must restore the Voting Rights Act and, during the pandemic, we must ensure that USPS has the resources needed to deliver ballots cast by mail this fall.

retweeted_text: Join us this Saturday, Dec. 7 for Storytime with a Congresswoman! Congresswoman Kendra Horn will read a story and answer questions about what it's like to be a public servant. There will also be playtime and a craft. This is a non-partisan event. https://t.co/PHjgTZjmvQ https://t.co/DU4tCGY4mp

full_text: Enough is enough. Today the House passed legislation to stop scam robocalls by stepping up enforcement against robocallers and increasing access to call-authentication. This is another example of what we can accomplish when we work in a bipartisan way. Let's pass this into law! https://t.co/4SgnCLtEdR

full_text: Today I co-sponsored the No Budget No Pay Act - the idea is simple: if Congress doesn't meet deadlines for budget and funding bills, then members don't get paid. It's time for Congress to stop kicking the can down the road and meet it's constitutional responsibilities. https://t.co/JCgTBFoKxi
